doc_summary_long: Gen John Nicholson says he's facing a shortfall of troops necessary for training Afghan forces and warns about increasing support from Russia for Taliban The commander of the US war in Afghanistan has requested several thousand new troops for America's longest-ever conflict to break what he described as a stalemate. In the first indication of the future course of the 15-year-old war under Donald Trump, army Gen John Nicholson told a Senate panel that he was facing a shortfall of troops necessary for training Afghan forces to ultimately replace their US and Nato counterparts.
doc_summary_short: Gen John Nicholson says he's facing a shortfall of troops necessary for training Afghan forces and warns about increasing support from Russia for Taliban
doc_title: US commander in Afghanistan requests several thousand new troops
